string-array.item:
Operations are used to perform operations on variables and values.

 In the following example, we use the + operator to add together two values:

 Int x = 100 + 50;
 150 = (100 + 50)

 Taking this idea further, variables and values can be added together as well as variables and other variables. The example below shows this in action 

 int sum1 = 100 + 50;
 150 = (100 + 50)

 int sum2 = sum1 + 250;
 400 = (150 + 250)

 int sum3 = sum2 + sum2;
 800 = (400 + 400)

If (condition) {\n\n
//Code in here will be run only if the condition is true.\n\n
}

If (condition) {


    //Code in here will be run only if the condition is true.


} else {


    //Code in here will be run only if the condition is False.


}

If (Condition1) { 


    //block of code to be run if Condition1 is true 


} else if (Condition 2) {


    //block of code to be run if Condition1 is false and Condition2 is true 


} else {


    //block of code to be run if Conditon1 is false and Condition2 is false 


}

While (Condition) {\n\n
    //code block to be run. \n\n
}

For (Statement1; Statement2; Statement3) {

 //code to be run

 } 


Statement1 is run (one time) before the code block is run.


Statement2 defines the condition for running the code block.


Statement3 is executed (Every time) after the code block has to be Executed.
